      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's not just that you made two cups; the silence is the real killer here. You're stuck in a loop where your actions feel pointless because the person who matters to you isn't there to witness them. The house is loud with the lack of connection, and you're just using coffee to numb the pain.\nThe only way out of this heavy, pointless existence is to stop caring about the empty chair and start caring about yourself. You deserve a morning where your actions matter, not because someone else is watching.\nStop waiting for someone to show up and make the silence finally bearable. Your life has value right now, even if you don't see it yet.",
