    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not about \"caring about myself.\" that sounds so hollow. how am i supposed to care about a life that's just half a person? it feels like i'm just a ghost wandering through a museum of things we used to do. every day is just a repetitive, meaningless chore to keep a body moving that doesn't even want to be here. everything feels so empty. it's like there's no point to any of it anymore.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are not a ghost haunting a museum; you are a person who has lost the ability to feel the present moment because the person who mattered is gone. The emptiness you feel is not a flaw in your life, but a direct result of the absence of the one who was supposed to fill it. You are stuck in a loop of repetition because you are waiting for a connection that no longer exists, and that waiting is the only thing keeping you alive. To stop feeling this way, you must acknowledge that your life still matters even without the other half, and that the only way to break this cycle is to stop looking for someone to complete you and start living for yourself right now.",
